<main>
    <section id="intro">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>TaskMaster is a powerful, easy-to-use task management application designed to help individuals and teams stay organized and on top of their responsibilities. This documentation will guide you through installation, features, and usage.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="getting-started">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <h3>Installation</h3>
            <p>To get started with TaskMaster, follow these steps:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Download TaskMaster from the <a href="#">official website</a>.</li>
                <li>Install the application on your system following the on-screen instructions.</li>
                <li>Open the app and sign in using your account credentials or create a new account.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3>First Steps</h3>
            <p>Once installed, you can start creating tasks, setting deadlines, and organizing them into projects. The main interface is intuitive, with options to add, edit, or remove tasks.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features">
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <h3>Task Management</h3>
            <p>Organize your tasks into projects, set priorities, and track progress using a visual board.</p>

            <h3>Team Collaboration</h3>
            <p>Share tasks with your team, assign them to different members, and monitor their progress.</p>

            <h3>Notifications</h3>
            <p>Get reminders for upcoming deadlines, overdue tasks, and team updates.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="api">
        <h2>API Reference</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <p>The TaskMaster API allows you to automate tasks, integrate with third-party tools, and customize your workflows.</p>
            <h3>Authentication</h3>
            <pre><code>POST /api/v1/login</code></pre>
            <p>Use this endpoint to authenticate users and obtain a session token.</p>

            <h3>Creating a Task</h3>
            <pre><code>POST /api/v1/tasks</code></pre>
            <p>Create a new task by providing the task details in the request body.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="section-content">
            <h3>How do I reset my password?</h3>
            <p>If you've forgotten your password, go to the login screen and click "Forgot password" to receive a reset link via email.</p>

            <h3>Can I use TaskMaster offline?</h3>
            <p>Currently, TaskMaster requires an internet connection to sync tasks across devices. Offline functionality is coming in a future release.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
